                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->
                  <br>
                  <div class="margin">
                      <h2>Trouble Shooting</h2>
                      <p><strong>Mobile Accesspoints</strong> - 3G / LTE Router which use a SIM-card often don´t get an IP-Address which is needed for the DDNS-Service. If you use a mobile internet connection on the network of your camera and you´re not able to access it through the internet, you should ask your provider if it is possible to get a WAN IP. Most of the bussiness contracts usually offer this option. A public IP-Address is needed to access the camera by using DDNS.</p>
                      <p>Another problem cause could be a <strong>DS-Lite</strong> (Dual Stack Lite) connection. It is not possible to access your camera via DDNS if you are using DS-Lite. This is the case if your provider is using IPv6-addresses instead of IPv4-addresses. You can check <a href="http://www.wieistmeineip.de/">here</a>, if you have an IPv4-address.</p>
                      <p>If you´re using a <strong>mobile Accesspoint</strong> or <strong>IPv6</strong> with your camera, there is only one solution for the remote access. All of our HD-Cameras have a Point-2-Point UserID (P2P UID), which makes remote access possible no matter which internet conection you use with your camera.</p>
                      <p>Another reason why you can´t remotely access your camera via DDNS might be the <strong>Kindersicherung (child safety device)</strong> of your FritzBox. You can check in the list for the child safety for your camera and grant it <strong>unbeschränkt (unlimited)</strong> access.</p>
